
// This Hyperlambda code checks two conditions using the [and] slot. It first verifies if the value of the node pointed to by the expression [mt:x:@.arguments/*/max] is greater than 0. Then, it checks if any nodes exist at the path specified by [exists:x:@sort/0]. Both conditions must be true for the [and] slot to evaluate to true.
and
   mt:x:@.arguments/*/max
      .:int:0
   exists:x:@sort/0
